page.content:
{For elderly and infirm:}              
 HOME HELPS: housework for disabled;   
 DISTRICT NURSES: home nursing;        
 MEALS ON WHEELS: volunteers cook and  
 deliver 12 meals 3 times a week @ 70p;
 LUNCHEON CLUB: volunteers cook and    
 serve 24 meals @70p in Hall for those 
 living on their own, alternate weeks; 
 AID IN SICKNESS FUND: home nursing    
 items, cash for hospital visits, etc; 
 LEISURE CENTRE: recreation and social 
 club with refreshments every Friday;  
 SILVER THREADS: social club for talks 
 and outings twice a month on Tuesdays;
 CHIROPODY: mobile clinic monthly.     
 Most rely  largely, or in part, on    
 voluntary workers, also for contact   
 between services and those in need.   
{Other services:}                      
 LIBRARY: County LEA opens twice a week
 with home delivery service for infirm;
 BABY CLINIC: Every other Thursday
